deck: Grady Lyda was a graphic and technical aerospace artist. Using the nickname Gray he published several short comics stories in various publications in the mid to late 1970s.
description:
Personal Life

Born Grady Luther Lyda III, Gray Lyda published several short graphic stories in the Star*Reach anthology series in the mid 1970s. Although he would leave comics to be a graphic designer for the aerospace industry the handful of Tempus Fugit stories he wrote and drew left a lasting impression.

Comics Work

All of Lyda's comics work was published in the early issues of the Star*Reach anthology series.
name: Gray Lyda

description:
Marco Renna was born in Brindisi in 1989, he remained there until 2010, when he moved to Bologna.

He graduated from the International School of Comics of Reggio Emilia. Later, in collaboration with some writers he published some short stories for the digital magazine Sbam! Comics and for Future Quake Press on Something Wicked. In 2015 he made his debut in the American market as the penciler for Action Lab Comics for an issue of Actionverse and for the The F1rst Hero: Wednesday's Child mini-series.

In 2016 he won the Top Cow Talent Hunt as a Runner-up.

Currently he works for Aspen Comics as a penciller for the series All New Micheal Turner's Fathom.
name: Marco Renna
